I'm from Kochi prefecture, but I currently live in Poland.
My favorite hobbies are watching movies, taking walks, and learning languages.
I'm currently learning English, French, Korean, and Polish.
I've studied abroad in Wales(UK), France, and Korea.

I'm from Nagano prefecture, and now I live in Saitama prefecture. I studied abroad in America.

I'm currently learning Korean.  I would like to visit Korea and North Europe.

My favorite hobbies include traveling and reading.  My favorite animal is the sea otter.  My favorite manga is Yotsuba&!

I am the founder of Comprehensible Japanese. I live in Fukuoka, Japan with my husband and two kids. I studied abroad in Tasmania, Australia for 10 months in 2006. I love learning languages through Comprehensible Input. I’m currently learning English, Korean and Mandarin.

I'm from Miyazaki prefecture, and now I live in Toronto, Canada, studying English. I previously worked for a newspaper company in Japan for 5 years. I like minimalism. I'm interested in Japanese and world history.

I live in Japan with my American husband and our daughter. 

I speak Japanese and English.  I've been to New Zealand, America (Studied for a year), France, Spain, Italy, Indonesia, and Saipan.

I like writing blogs, dancing, eating, traveling and reading Manga.  I hate frogs, lamb meat, peas, and horror movies.

I was born and raised in Japan, originally from Tokyo, and I still live in Tokyo. I've also lived in the United States and Singapore. I love creating things and have been maintaining my YouTube channel and Instagram for a long time! I'm studying English and Korean. Nice to meet you :)

I live in Tuscany, Italy. My hobbies are sketching, paper embroidery, and collecting stones. In my free time, I hang out with my cat. I like looking up at the moon in the morning. I would like to see Manhattanhenge someday. I majored in Japanese language and culture in college and graduate school. I have been teaching Japanese since 2014. I am really happy to be a part of CIJ! I look forward to working with you all.

I was born and raised in Tokyo. I studied English in Canada and have also studied a little Korean and Spanish. My passion at CIJ is sharing Japanese culture with everyone. I love surfing, dogs, and Pokémon!
ウクレレを弾きながら歌います。犬の友だちがいます。そして本の虫です。日本茶と日本のご飯なしでは生きられません。I sing and play the ukelele. I have doggo friends. I am a bookworm🐛. And I can't live without Japanese tea and rice.

I'm from Aichi Prefecture, but now I live in Taiwan with my wife and learn Mandarin Chinese through daily life. I've worked as a chef in Japan and Australia, and as a ski instructor in Japan. I love traveling, cooking, meeting different people, and exploring beautiful places!

If you have any issues or ideas for improvement, please let me know via [the contact page](/contact), Discord (username = bennycopter), or the [Community Site](https://community.cijapanese.com).

My favorite hobbies include D&D, video games, and building things.  My favorite anime are One Piece, Polar Bear Cafe, and Bobobo-bo Bo-bobo.  My favorite music is whatever genre [Toehider](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1vdaVqASI_8) is.  My favorite author is [Ajahn Brahm](https://www.amazon.com/dp/0733635032/).  My favorite animator is [Worthikids](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GyCagepF_T4).  I'd like to visit Japan someday.
